      • Serialized Fields

          String comments
          Additional comments provided by the user in the review.
        • dairyScore
          @Range(min=1L,max=5L) Integer dairyScore
          The dairy allergy score assigned by the user in the review. Score should be between 1 and 5, inclusive.
        • eggScore
          @Range(min=1L,max=5L) Integer eggScore
          The egg allergy score assigned by the user in the review. Score should be between 1 and 5, inclusive.

          The unique identifier of the review.
        • peanutScore
          @Range(min=1L,max=5L) Integer peanutScore
          The peanut allergy score assigned by the user in the review. Score should be between 1 and 5, inclusive.
        • restaurantId
          @NotNull Long restaurantId
          The unique identifier of the restaurant being reviewed. This field must not be null.
        • status
          String status
          The status of the review represented by a string. It is automatically set to "PENDING" when a new review is created. An admin can update the status to "APPROVED" or "REJECTED".
        • username
          @NotNull String username
          The username of the user who created the review. This field must not be null.

        • zipcode
          @Pattern(message="Invalid Zip Code",regexp="^[0-9]{5}(?:-[0-9]{4})?$") String zipcode
          The user's zip code. It must match the regular expression pattern for valid zip codes. Valid zip codes are 5 digits, optionally followed by a hyphen and 4 more digits.
